text.text: Porto Trindade Hotel's strength is its excellent location near the old town and Metro. Our room was quiet and spacious, but also pretty dirty with an outdated mattress and old furniture. Breakfast was very decent, but the hotel's decor feels dated. Some staff interactions could be improved, and while it may not be perfect for long stays, its central position is a perk.

text.text: Just few minutes walk from the main Trindade station and 10 minutes walk to the main city, very convenient! Room is big and clean and sufficient air-con! Buffett breakfast is few hot food to pastry to fresh food, good to kick start for the morning!
